sec.p:
The ANSYS ACP PrepPost module was used to define the layup on the wheel. Three epoxy prepreg materials were defined. For the disc, Park Aerospace HTS45E23/E-752-LT material was used. For the rims, Delta-Preg T700/DT806R UD fabric and T300/DT806R 2 × 2 twill fabric was used. Material properties are given in Table 2. The layup was defined in three zones: rims (inner and outer), disc and spokes (see Fig. 4a). Figure 4b depicts the fibre directions for each of these zones. Given the large number of design variables, the layup optimisation was simplified using geometric constraints. As shown in Fig. 4, the outer rim was sized to fit the tyre valve with clearance for attaching a pump head. The rim thickness was set close to 4 mm to allow for installation of snap-in-valves as per the standard. This then constrained the disc thickness to approximately 10 mm to achieve the required mounting offset.Table 2
