The pressure on the wheel was evaluated for the bump and cornering load cases. As shown in Fig. 9, a maximum of 30.84 MPa and 49.25 MPa was found for the bump and cornering load cases respectively. Given the 90° compressive strength of 341 MPa for the material (as provided by the manufacturer), the maximum stress failure criterion coefficient can be found as follows [26]:Fig. 9
